
{{#question}}
<script>
    $(function() {
        $('#pl-matrix-component-input-{{uuid}} [data-toggle="popover"]').popover({
            sanitize: false,
            container: 'body',
            template: '<div class="popover pl-matrix-component-input-popover" role="tooltip"><div class="arrow"></div><h3 class="popover-header"></h3><div class="popover-body"></div></div>',
        });
    });
</script>

<span class="form-inline d-inline-block ml-2 pl-matrix-component-span-fullwidth">
    <div id="pl-matrix-component-input-{{uuid}}" class="input-group">
        <span class="input-group-prepend">
            {{#label}}<label class="input-group-text" id="basic-addon2">{{{label}}}</label>{{/label}}
        </span>
        <div class="form-control" >
            {{{input_array}}}
        </div>
        <div class="input-group-append">
            <a role="button" class="btn btn-light border d-flex align-items-center" data-toggle="popover" data-html="true" title="Matrix" data-content="{{info}}" data-placement="auto" data-trigger="focus" tabindex="0">
                <i class="fa fa-question-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                {{#correct}}&nbsp;<span class="badge badge-success"><i class="fa fa-check" aria-hidden="true"></i> 100%</span>{{/correct}}
                {{#partial}}&nbsp;<span class="badge badge-warning"><i class="far fa-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i> {{partial}}%</span>{{/partial}}
                {{#incorrect}}&nbsp;<span class="badge badge-danger"><i class="fa fa-times" aria-hidden="true"></i> 0%</span>{{/incorrect}}

            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</span>
{{/question}}

{{#submission}}

<div class="d-inline-block ml-2">

{{#error}}
<script>
    $(function(){
        $('#pl-matrix-component-input-submission-{{uuid}} [data-toggle="popover"]').popover({
            sanitize: false,
            container: 'body',
            template: '<div class="popover pl-matrix-component-input-popover" role="tooltip"><div class="arrow"></div><h3 class="popover-header"></h3><div class="popover-body"></div></div>',
        });
    });
</script>
<span id="pl-matrix-component-input-submission-{{uuid}}" class="pl-matrix-component-input-invalid">

{{#parse_error}}
    {{#label}}<span>{{{label}}}</span>{{/label}}

    {{#raw_submitted_answer}}{{{raw_submitted_answer}}}{{/raw_submitted_answer}}

    <span class="badge text-danger badge-invalid"><i class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle" aria-hidden="true"></i> Invalid</span>

    <a href="javascript:void(0);" role="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-secondary small border" data-placement="auto" data-trigger="focus" data-toggle="popover" data-html="true" style="margin-left: 5px" title="Format Error" tabindex="0" data-content="{{parse_error}}"> Why <i class="fa fa-question-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i></a>
{{/parse_error}}
{{#missing_input}}
    {{#label}}<span>{{{label}}}</span>{{/label}}

    <span class="badge text-dark badge-missing-input"><i class="fa fa-question-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i> Missing Input</span>

    <a href="javascript:void(0);" role="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-secondary small border" data-placement="auto" data-trigger="focus" data-toggle="popover" data-html="true" style="margin-left: 5px" title="Missing Input" tabindex="0" data-content="There is no submitted value for this field.  This may have happened because the question was changed by course staff after the answer was submitted."> Why <i class="fa fa-question-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    </a>
{{/missing_input}}

</span>
{{/error}}

{{^error}}
{{#a_sub}}
{{#label}}{{{label}}}{{/label}}
{{a_sub}}
{{#correct}}<span class="badge badge-success"><i class="fa fa-check" aria-hidden="true"></i> 100%</span>{{/correct}}
{{#partial}}<span class="badge badge-warning"><i class="far fa-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i> {{partial}}%</span>{{/partial}}
{{#incorrect}}<span class="badge badge-danger"><i class="fa fa-times" aria-hidden="true"></i> 0%</span>{{/incorrect}}
{{/a_sub}}
{{#a_sub_feedback}}{{{a_sub_feedback}}}{{/a_sub_feedback}}
{{/error}}

</div>

{{/submission}}

{{#answer}}
<div class="d-inline-block ml-2" id="pl-matrix-component-input-answer-{{uuid}}">
    {{#label}}<span>{{{label}}}</span>{{/label}}
    <samp id="latex-data-{{uuid}}">{{latex_data}}</samp>
</div>
{{/answer}}

{{#format}}
<p>
Your must enter all the components of the matrix.
</p>
<p>
Each entry must be a real number between <code>-1e308</code> and <code>1e308</code> (i.e., it must be interpretable as a double-precision floating-point number).
No symbolic expressions (those that involve {{^allow_fractions}}fractions, {{/allow_fractions}}square roots, variables, etc.) will be accepted. Scientific notation is accepted (e.g., <code>1.2e03</code>). {{#allow_fractions}}Fractions are accepted.{{/allow_fractions}}
</p>
<p>
{{#relabs}}Numbers must be accurate to within relative tolerance <code>{{rtol}}</code> and absolute tolerance <code>{{atol}}</code>.{{/relabs}}
{{#sigfig}}Numbers must be accurate to {{digits}} significant figures. This means (for example) that if the true answer is <code>1.234</code>, then the submitted answer must be between <code>1.234 - {{comparison_eps}}</code> and <code>1.234 + {{comparison_eps}}</code> to be counted correct.{{/sigfig}}
{{#decdig}}Numbers must be accurate to {{digits}} digits after the decimal. This means (for example) that if the true answer is <code>1.234</code>, then the submitted answer must be between <code>1.234 - {{comparison_eps}}</code> and <code>1.234 + {{comparison_eps}}</code> to be counted correct.{{/decdig}}
</p>
{{/format}}

{{#shortformat}}
{{#relabs}}(rtol={{rtol}}, atol={{atol}}){{/relabs}}{{#sigfig}}({{digits}} significant figures){{/sigfig}}{{#decdig}}({{digits}} digits after decimal){{/decdig}}
{{/shortformat}}

{{#format_error}}
    <p> Invalid format: one or more entries of the submitted answer could not be interpreted as a decimal number.  No symbolic expressions (those that involve {{^allow_fractions}}fractions,{{/allow_fractions}} square roots, variables, etc.) will be accepted. Scientific notation is accepted. {{#allow_fractions}}Fractions are accepted.{{/allow_fractions}} </p>
    <p> Example <i>valid</i> inputs: <code class="user-output">5</code> &nbsp; <code class="user-output">-17.3</code> &nbsp; <code class="user-output">4.25e7</code> </p>
    <p> Example <i>invalid</i> inputs: <code class="user-output">2/3</code> &nbsp; <code class="user-output">6+9</code> &nbsp; <code class="user-output">4*10^7</code> &nbsp; <code class="user-output">3*pi</code> &nbsp; <code class="user-output">3.6i</code> </p>
    <hr>
    <small>
        <p> You must enter all the components of the matrix. </p>
        <p> Each entry of the submitted answer must be formatted as a <i>double-precision floating-point</i> number.  These numbers lie roughly in the range of -1.79 &times; 10<sup>308</sup> to 1.79 &times; 10<sup>308</sup>. </p>
    </small>
{{/format_error}}
